com.nerjal.json.parser.options

Class ObjectParseOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nerjal.json.parser.options.ObjectParseOptions

  • public class ObjectParseOptions
extends Object

    Stringification options for JsonObject elements.

    Allows to set whether should the object be stringified using unquoted, simple quoted or double quoted keys.

    Hence only three formats for objects' stringification are available, each only affecting the stringification of the object's keys.

    Default is double-quoted keys, in order to better fit to JSON4 standards, for a better compatibility.
    Author:
    Nerjal Nosk
